Cook,<br><br>
Your post noted.  I am not aware of all that has gone before.  You post reminded me to look back and reflect.  Responding to the specific without reflection to the sum.<br><br>
The statement about children is my achilles heel.  John caught me at a weak moment.  The ideas that we leave behind and what our children and others children think is important to me.  I fail to remember they are capable of their own assumptions.<br><br>
My children read this site, but the youngest is a 26 year old intellectual.  He understands completely.  He has formed his own opinions of these posts and is most concerned with the pain some cause me.<br><br>
We are planting the seed of truth in a fertile field.  It is our duty to tend to this crop.  The truth is the only element which will let our contribution be part of the record which lives after us.  I have read much of the remanufactured history of other times and fear we may suffer the same fate.<br><br>
SW
